Karen Pence, the wife of Vice President Mike Pence, has returned to teaching art classes for children at an elementary school in Northern Virginia. She will be teaching twice a week at Immanuel Christian School until May. Mrs. Pence expressed her excitement about being back in the classroom and doing what she loves. She has 25 years of experience as an elementary school teacher, including 12 years as an art teacher at Immanuel Christian School. Mrs. Pence holds a B.S. and M.S. in Elementary Education from Butler University and is an award-winning watercolor artist.